<span id="freeTextContainer4297065785303196759"><strong>Fluffy, silly, and fun</strong><br/><br/>The Malloreon books are, let&apos;s be honest, not incredibly well written. All the main characters have started to sound the same, they all use the same idioms and expressions, and things got far too well for them. It&apos;s like a band of Mary Sues. <br/><br/>I still love this book. <br/><br/>It&apos;s fun to read, the events and writing are fun and good enough to be enjoyable. It&apos;s not war and peace, but it&apos;s still a fun read. </span>
  <span id="freeText4297065785303196759" style="display:none"><strong>Fluffy, silly, and fun</strong><br /><br />The Malloreon books are, let's be honest, not incredibly well written. All the main characters have started to sound the same, they all use the same idioms and expressions, and things got far too well for them. It's like a band of Mary Sues. <br /><br />I still love this book. <br /><br />It's fun to read, the events and writing are fun and good enough to be enjoyable. It's not war and peace, but it's still a fun read. </span>
