<div id="review_2215349067" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2215349067" />
    <a title="Zach P." class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/73329732-zach-p"><img alt="Zach P." src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1509986040p2/73329732.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2215349067?book_show_action=true">Dec 15, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Zach P." class="user" itemprop="url" name="Zach P." href="/user/show/73329732-zach-p">Zach P.</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2215349067" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15290503103285432358">The Sorceress of Darshiva,book four of the Malloreon series, by David Eddings is about a man named Belgarion who gathers a large group of differently talented people and they go to catch the thief who kidnapped Belgarion&apos;s son to fulfill the dark prophecy instead of the light. however, the thief isn&apos;t the only thing they have to worry about. Their party is also being chased by an over-religious disciple of the dark god Torak who Belgarion killed in the previous series, The Belgariad. As Belgario</span>
  <span id="freeText15290503103285432358" style="display:none">The Sorceress of Darshiva,book four of the Malloreon series, by David Eddings is about a man named Belgarion who gathers a large group of differently talented people and they go to catch the thief who kidnapped Belgarion's son to fulfill the dark prophecy instead of the light. however, the thief isn't the only thing they have to worry about. Their party is also being chased by an over-religious disciple of the dark god Torak who Belgarion killed in the previous series, The Belgariad. As Belgarion and his party chase the thief, they're being chased by the fleet lead by the disciple, and the malloreon army lead by king Zakath of Mallorea.<br /><br />Belgarion is the king of a small isle west of the Seven Kingdoms, and is included in the four countries of the Alorns. along with being the king, he's also the child of light chosen by the prophecy and is the overlord of the west. Belgarion has special abilities called sorcery to do special things like translocate, will somthing to be, and a lot of other things. he was taught by his grand mother and great grand father slowly to use sorcery. As the series goes on, he gets stronger and can do more things. although he has lots of problems, such as his son being stolen or the world being taken over by an evil god, he pulls through with his wife and son.<br /><br />In my opinion, this book from the series is great and leads straight into the next, and last, book of the series. The book has a lot of suspense and excitement and is fun to read. every page is packed with details and gives you a very good image.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15290503103285432358" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


